# Module System

## Protocol (ModuleProtocol.swift)

Every module conforms to `VibeNotchModule`. All methods have default implementations returning nil/empty, so you only override what you need.

**Required properties:**
```swift
var identifier: ModuleIdentifier { get }
var displayName: String { get }
var icon: String { get }                    // SF Symbol name
var objectDidChange: (() -> Void)? { get set }
```

**Optional overrides:**
```swift
func activate() / deactivate()              // Lifecycle
func refresh() / displayChanged()           // Reactive updates
func closedLeadingView(for displayUUID: String) -> NotchSlotContent?   // Left slot in closed notch
func closedTrailingView(for displayUUID: String) -> NotchSlotContent?  // Right slot in closed notch
func expandedWidgets(for displayUUID: String) -> [NotchExpandedWidget] // Widgets in expanded panel
func statusBarContent() -> StatusBarContent?                           // Menu bar icon/label
func menuSections() -> [ModuleMenuSection]                             // Context menu items
func makeSettingsView() -> AnyView?                                    // Settings panel
```

## Data Flow

```
Module.closedLeadingView(displayUUID) → NotchSlotContent
  ↓
ModuleRegistry.aggregatedLeadingSlots(displayUUID)
  ↓
NotchSurfaceController → YabaiNotchViewModel
  ↓
NotchSurfaceView renders
```

## Creating a New Module

### 1. Create module class (`Sources/VibeNotch/{Name}Module.swift`)
```swift
@MainActor
final class MyModule: ObservableObject, VibeNotchModule {
    let identifier = ModuleIdentifier("com.vibenotch.mymodule")
    let displayName = "My Module"
    let icon = "star.fill"
    var objectDidChange: (() -> Void)?

    // Only override methods you need:
    func expandedWidgets(for displayUUID: String) -> [NotchExpandedWidget] { ... }
    func makeSettingsView() -> AnyView? { AnyView(MySettingsView(module: self)) }
}
```

### 2. Create views (`Sources/VibeNotch/{Name}Views.swift`)
Self-contained views. Use `@ObservedObject var module: MyModule` for data binding.

### 3. Register in AppModel.startIfNeeded()
```swift
let myModule = MyModule()
moduleRegistry.register(myModule)
```

### 4. Build & test
```bash
swift build && swift test && bash scripts/build-app.sh
```

## Key Types

- `NotchSlotContent` — AnyView + width for closed notch slots
- `NotchExpandedWidget` — id, moduleID, estimatedHeight, content for expanded panel
- `StatusBarContent` — icon, label, tooltip, length for menu bar
- `ModuleMenuSection` — title + [NSMenuItem] for context menu

## Reference Modules

- **TodoListModule** — Simplest, self-contained, no external APIs (~180 lines)
- **JiraModule** — API integration pattern with timer refresh
- **AIQuotaModule** — Status bar + trailing slot indicator pattern
